        Explore Batches →
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════
     FAQs
══════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="faqs" class="py-16 px-6">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="reveal mb-12 text-center">
      <p class="text-brand-400 text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">Common Questions</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-4xl font-800 text-white">QA Test FAQs</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      {[
        { q: "Are these QA sectional tests free?", a: "Yes — all 4 QA tests are completely free with no signup fee. Click any 'Start Test' button to begin immediately." },
        { q: "How many questions and what is the marking scheme?", a: "Each test has 22 questions — approximately 14 MCQs (with −1 negative marking) and 8 TITA questions (no negative marking). Correct MCQ answers get +3 marks, same as the real CAT." },
        { q: "What QA topics are covered across the 4 tests?", a: "Together the 4 tests cover Arithmetic (percentages, profit/loss, time-speed, averages, mixtures), Algebra (quadratics, functions, inequalities, progressions), Geometry (triangles, circles, co-ordinate geometry), and Modern Math (P&C, probability, number systems, set theory)." },
        { q: "Are the questions of actual CAT difficulty?", a: "Yes. Tests 1 and 2 are at moderate-to-medium CAT difficulty (targeting 80th–90th %ile aspirants), while Tests 3 and 4 ramp up to 95th–99th %ile difficulty." },
        { q: "Can I retake tests?", a: "Yes, unlimited retakes. We recommend retaking a test after targeted topic revision to see a measurable score jump." },
        { q: "Will I receive detailed solutions?", a: "Yes — every question comes with a step-by-step solution, alternative approaches, and time benchmarks immediately after you submit the test." },
      ].map((faq, i) => (
        <div class="reveal glass rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
          <button class="faq-btn w-full text-left px-7 py-5 flex items-start justify-between gap-4" data-index={i}>
            <span class="font-display font-700 text-white text-sm leading-relaxed">{faq.q}</span>
            <span class="faq-icon text-brand-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 text-lg">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-body hidden px-7 pb-6">
            <p class="text-ink-200 text-sm leading-relaxed">{faq.a}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

